    public class HuffmanCoding.BTNode<F extends java.lang.Comparable<F>,S extends java.lang.Comparable<S>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<HuffmanCoding.BTNode<F,S>>
    Binary Tree Node class, used for the construction of a huffman tree. Each node contains to fields: a frequency of type F that corresponds to the amount of times a symbol is present in the text to be encoded, and a symbol of type S that corresponds to a character present in the text to be encoded. Edges in the tree only point in one direction, that is from parent to child. Every BTNode only has to children, one left and one right.
    Author:
    Abdiel Cortés
